      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BORACAY PLAYER (4) scored his maiden success two back then hit the frame last time when second and beaten 1.5 lengths at this track over 320m (18.53). Back to track where he won his maiden. In form and looks a top chance again. MIAMI VICE (7) was below best last time when fourth but three back was a Grade 5 winner in quick time at this track. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Can find the frame this time. TELL ME ENOUGH (2) was safely held last time out, finishing fifth at this track over 400m behind Soda Mish (23.70) in a Grade 5. Placed at his previous run. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings four times from six attempts. Key runner who gets his chance to atone. OUT OF LUCK (5) is in the mix after placing last time out.",
